The paper deals with object detection and recognition in first-person (egocentric) videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed pipeline involves deep learning techniques, specifically region-based convolutional neural networks (R-CNN), which is a popular method in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of motion cues and feature fusion, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's focus on object manipulation suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO).
